1
00:00:00,480 --> 00:00:07,800
In any market, price moves from supply zones 
to demand zones and back: over and over again. 

2
00:00:08,580 --> 00:00:14,220
If you learn to find these zones, you can 
get into decent trades, precisely at the  

3
00:00:14,220 --> 00:00:20,040
point when banks start to place their trades.
That’s why today I’m sharing one of my favorite  

4
00:00:20,040 --> 00:00:26,400
smart money strategies, using supply and demand 
areas, in combination with psychological levels. 

5
00:00:26,940 --> 00:00:31,680
You know the drill, like, subscribe 
and stick around for the full video.

6
00:00:32,460 --> 00:00:37,020
Supply and Demand 

7
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:43,080
Demand Zones form when banks place 
a large number of buy positions.  

8
00:00:43,740 --> 00:00:48,720
This creates an imbalance, and results 
in the price aggressively moving higher. 

9
00:00:49,740 --> 00:00:53,160
These are the support levels 
of supply and demand trading. 

10
00:00:54,420 --> 00:01:00,960
Supply zones are points where the banks place a 
significant number of sell positions, resulting  

11
00:01:00,960 --> 00:01:06,960
in price aggressively moving lower.
These are the resistance points  

12
00:01:06,960 --> 00:01:11,580
where price could fall.
So if price returns to  

13
00:01:11,580 --> 00:01:17,040
certain supply and demand zones, it has a 
high probability of rejecting these areas.

14
00:01:19,080 --> 00:01:25,680
Let’s be clear, it takes time, practice, and 
experience to identify the best supply and  

15
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:28,800
demand areas to trade.
Here’s MY process. 

16
00:01:29,520 --> 00:01:33,060
You already know that supply 
and demand zones are formed  

17
00:01:33,060 --> 00:01:36,840
when banks are placing large quantities of orders. 

18
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:42,900
Well, on a price chart, a sharp rise, 
or a sharp decline, appears in price. 

19
00:01:44,340 --> 00:01:47,700
These are the first signs 
that smart money are active.

20
00:01:47,700 --> 00:01:57,300
Market imbalances
Identifying market imbalances is the first step to  

21
00:01:57,300 --> 00:02:04,080
finding supply and demand zones. Market imbalances 
refer to big price shifts in one direction. 

22
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:09,720
To locate demand zones, you 
look for fast impulse move. 

23
00:02:10,260 --> 00:02:17,700
The key point to remember while finding the market 
imbalances is to keep an eye on big green candles. 

24
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:24,660
You can identify these candles by their 
long bodies with little to no wicks. 

25
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:32,760
Once you have identified a fast impulse move, it 
becomes a lot easier to find the base of the zone. 

26
00:02:33,660 --> 00:02:40,920
You find the most recent down candle before the 
impulse move and place a line at its high price,  

27
00:02:41,760 --> 00:02:46,560
and a line at the most recent swing low, 
that formed at the source of the move. 

28
00:02:47,640 --> 00:02:52,260
It’s a slightly different method to draw 
the area, compared to my previous videos,  

29
00:02:52,260 --> 00:02:56,580
but I’ll explain later why I 
choose to use this method instead.

30
00:02:58,080 --> 00:03:02,760
To find supply zones, first, 
you’re looking for fast declines. 

31
00:03:03,540 --> 00:03:09,900
Sharp declines occur when supply comes into 
the market, which happens when the banks sell. 

32
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:17,760
Again, you look for big red candles, 
with long bodies and little or no wicks. 

33
00:03:17,760 --> 00:03:21,060
In theory, price has a high probability  

34
00:03:21,060 --> 00:03:25,440
of reversing once it returns 
to the source of the decline. 

35
00:03:26,340 --> 00:03:33,660
You then find the most recent up candle before the 
sharp down move and place a line at its low price,  

36
00:03:34,380 --> 00:03:39,780
and another line at the most recent swing 
high, that formed at the source of the move.

37
00:03:39,780 --> 00:03:45,480
psychological levels 

38
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:50,340
Human emotions play a part in the 
price action observed in markets. 

39
00:03:50,340 --> 00:03:56,160
Many traders prefer to set their “buy” 
and “sell” orders around round numbers. 

40
00:03:56,160 --> 00:04:01,380
It’s not that common to have 
an order placed at $60.12. 

41
00:04:02,820 --> 00:04:07,980
No, instead we like to work with round 
numbers, and that’s why these numbers  

42
00:04:07,980 --> 00:04:14,640
are psychological levels that have breakouts 
and big amounts of activity attached to them. 

43
00:04:15,420 --> 00:04:21,600
To plot these round numbers, I first add 
on Tradingview the horizontal grid lines. 

44
00:04:23,460 --> 00:04:28,440
Then I simply adjust the right 
margin, and play with the scale,  

45
00:04:29,460 --> 00:04:36,120
depending on the market I’m trading.
These psychological levels are perfect  

46
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:40,080
for identifying high probability 
supply and demand areas. 

47
00:04:40,740 --> 00:04:46,080
A supply zone, in combination with 
a psychological level, is a high  

48
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:53,280
probability area to initiate a buy position.
A demand zone, which includes psychological  

49
00:04:53,280 --> 00:04:58,500
level, again, offers a low risk - 
high reward sell situation.
 
 
 
 
 
  

50
00:05:00,540 --> 00:05:04,560
We are looking at Crude Oil.
I prefer to analyze higher time  

51
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:11,820
frames, and pinpoint the entry on lower ones.
On the daily time frame, I see a demand area. 

52
00:05:11,820 --> 00:05:19,620
I see this big strong lineup of candles moving 
up. Candles with long bodies and small wicks. 

53
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:26,460
We then identify the origin of the price movement, 
the last bearish candle before the rally. 

54
00:05:29,220 --> 00:05:34,980
We also adjust the scale on the right, to 
have a $1 grid, to find the round numbers. 

55
00:05:36,900 --> 00:05:44,280
Our demand zone includes 3 psychological 
levels at 64, 63 and 62 dollars. 

56
00:05:45,180 --> 00:05:51,600
We don’t know which one will hold. You can set 
a limit order at one level inside the zone,  

57
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:57,720
the aggressive entry, or you could wait for a 
price action signal to confirm the rejection,  

58
00:05:57,720 --> 00:06:02,220
the conservative method.
I prefer the second approach. 

59
00:06:02,220 --> 00:06:09,060
I look for pin bars or engulfing candles 
to form inside a zone, rejecting a  

60
00:06:09,060 --> 00:06:15,180
psychological number and then I enter.
Now, we determined our value area,  

61
00:06:15,180 --> 00:06:22,200
let’s see if price returns to it.
We move the M15 time frame, to pinpoint the entry. 

62
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:37,500
This is the signal. A pin bar candlestick forms 
right after price enters the zone and rejected the  

63
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:44,580
$63 round number. This is our signal to buy.
Stop loss below the demand zone.  

64
00:06:47,220 --> 00:06:51,900
Take profit, as usual, depending 
on recent market structure. I’ll  

65
00:06:51,900 --> 00:06:57,960
set my first target here, at $72, 
at this potential supply zone. 

66
00:07:02,100 --> 00:07:09,360
And the second target around $78 level, 
again, below this other supply zone.
 
 

67
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:32,400
We move to Bitcoin, on the H4 time 
frame. I see this potential supply zone,  

68
00:07:32,940 --> 00:07:38,340
after this aggressive down move.
The STRENGTH OF THE MOVE is very  

69
00:07:38,340 --> 00:07:44,820
important. The stronger the price moves away 
from a zone, the more out-of-balance supply  

70
00:07:44,820 --> 00:07:50,400
and demand are at that zone. It means 
a heavy order is placed by smart money. 

71
00:07:51,420 --> 00:07:56,460
You also must analyze how far the 
price moved away from the supply zone.  

72
00:07:57,240 --> 00:08:04,140
The longer the distance the price moves away from 
a zone before returning to that zone, the better. 

73
00:08:05,100 --> 00:08:09,960
First-time retrace to the supply 
zone is the strongest to enter. 

74
00:08:09,960 --> 00:08:17,040
Always make sure the zone is still “fresh” which 
means that after the initial creation of the zone,  

75
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:23,160
price has not come back to it yet.
Each time price revisits a supply zone,  

76
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:29,040
more and more previously unfilled orders 
are filled and the level is weakened. 

77
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:37,200
Ok, now let’s wait for a retrace back to our 
zone. Observe we have 3 psychological levels  

78
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:42,120
inside the area. So, again, we’ll 
wait for price action confirmation.

79
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:55,140
Here’s the rejection, an evening 
star candlestick formation. 

80
00:08:57,240 --> 00:09:04,260
Stop loss is placed above the supply zone.
And we’ll target this demand zone. 
 
 
 
 
  

81
00:09:13,740 --> 00:09:20,400
Let’s move to stock market. Tesla.
On hourly time frame we find the  

82
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:28,020
potential demand zone. We draw the zone based 
on last bearish candle before the sharp rally. 

83
00:09:30,300 --> 00:09:36,600
Now we’ll keep an eye on the future price 
movements to see if it retraces back to this  

84
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:43,020
demand level, because in theory there should be 
more buy orders waiting to get executed here. 

85
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:51,840
I set a $10 grid on this market, and observe 
that our demand zone includes 2 round numbers. 

86
00:09:54,780 --> 00:09:59,100
Now we’ll wait for a confirmation, because 
we don’t know which level will hold. 

87
00:10:00,540 --> 00:10:07,260
A good idea for confirmation is to wait for the 
first reaction on the round number, to see if the  

88
00:10:07,260 --> 00:10:12,960
price is strongly pushed away off that level.
I also want to see signs  

89
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:19,020
of weakness in price action:
• Momentum loss (decreasing candle range and body) 

90
00:10:19,020 --> 00:10:24,060
• And lower wicks on the candles 
when price is inside the demand zone 

91
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:36,240
Ok, price found support at this 
psychological level, inside the zone. 

92
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:42,060
The stop loss is placed just 
beyond the extreme of the zone. 

93
00:10:43,380 --> 00:10:53,100
The take-profit is the next major supply level, 
which would be right here. So I’ll set my target  

94
00:10:53,100 --> 00:11:00,960
a few cents below this area. The risk to reward 
ratio on this trade is quite good, around 6.
 

95
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:16,740
Like I said before, you can be 
aggressive and use limit orders.  

96
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:22,860
It’s a decent way of trading supply and demand, 
and you can be quite successful with it. 

97
00:11:23,640 --> 00:11:30,300
The problem is that a limit order entry provides 
NO confirmation that price will reverse from a  

98
00:11:30,300 --> 00:11:38,280
zone. You will blindly place the order at the edge 
or inside the zone and hope that price reverses. 

99
00:11:39,060 --> 00:11:45,180
This would not be a problem if all supply and 
demand zones worked all the time. But, they don’t! 

100
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:50,700
Price blasts through zones 
frequently, usually without stopping.  

101
00:11:50,700 --> 00:11:57,240
With the limit order entry, you cannot avoid this.
So, you’ll end up with many losing trades.  

102
00:11:58,320 --> 00:12:02,040
With the price action entry, 
however, things are different. 

103
00:12:02,640 --> 00:12:06,960
It’s better to find the supply or 
demand zone on the HIGHER TIME FRAME,  

104
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:12,480
wait for the price to come to this 
level, and see any acceptance or  

105
00:12:12,480 --> 00:12:19,680
rejection from this zone on a lower time frame.
You look for any reversal price action signal  

106
00:12:19,680 --> 00:12:25,200
on the lower time frame, rejecting the 
psychological number, inside the zone. 

107
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:31,500
And yes, you’ll have a delayed entry, 
sometimes not even inside the zone. 

108
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:37,080
But, in the long run, price action confirmation 
will save you from many losing trades.
  

109
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:44,640
We trade EUR/USD, on the hourly chart. 
This would be my minimum time frame  

110
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:51,060
to find supply and demand area.
I see this supply zone right here,  

111
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:57,180
which had a huge drop consisting 
of multiple bearish large candles. 

112
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:07,980
This supply zone also aligns with the current 
trend, which is down. So another tip would be  

113
00:13:07,980 --> 00:13:14,940
to trade zones in the direction of the main trend:
• If the trend is down, you look for supply areas 

114
00:13:14,940 --> 00:13:19,560
• If you have an uptrend, 
you search for demand zones 

115
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:29,940
We have 2 round numbers inside the 
zone. So, as usual, we’ll wait for  

116
00:13:29,940 --> 00:13:37,560
a clear rejection, inside the supply zone.
Let’s pinpoint the entry on the M15 time frame. 

117
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:51,720
Just as expected, price found resistance 
at the first round number inside the zone,  

118
00:13:52,380 --> 00:13:54,540
forming a pin bar candlestick. 

119
00:13:55,980 --> 00:14:01,980
This is the confirmation I needed. Stop 
loss on the other side of the supply zone. 

120
00:14:04,020 --> 00:14:08,880
Take profit, a few points below 
the next major demand zone,  

121
00:14:10,740 --> 00:14:15,120
which would be here.
A risk to reward ratio of over 4.

122
